radiographic_examinations.findings: Small bibasilar atelectasis. No pleural or pericardial effusion. 5.0 x 2.7 cm hypodense cystic lesion in the right anterior abdomen with local mass effect on the left hepatic lobe consistent with a lymphangioma or peritoneal inclusion cyst. The appendix is dilated to 11 mm with hyperemia and adjacent fat stranding, consistent with acute appendicitis.
